<HEADLINE>
SHOTGUN NEW WEAPON IN USC ARSENAL?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ After having so much trouble protecting the
quarterback against Florida State, USC might consider including the
shotgun formation in its offense in the near future.
</P>
<P>
   ``We may have to. Strategically that makes a lot of sense,'' USC
coach Paul Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said it wasn't a good idea to try the shotgun when the
Trojans were forced to switch guard Jason Grain to center the past
two games because of injuries to Matt McShane and Eric Denmon.
McShane (sprained knee ligament) returned against Florida State in
a reserve role, however, and might be able to start Saturday
against Arizona State.
</P>
<P>
   ``I hate to jump into that at this point,'' Hackett said.
``That's a whole other world. I'd like to get McShane and Denmon
back first.''
</P>
<P>
   Tailback Chad Morton, who re-strained his back against Florida
State, is not expected to practice today.
</P>
<P>
   __ Forgotten past: The confidence gained from USC's 3-0 start
has apparently evaporated thanks to the Trojans' 30-10 loss to
Florida State.
</P>
<P>
   ``Those three games don't mean much,'' wide receiver Billy
Miller said. ``Whatever happened in the past doesn't matter.
(Florida State) was a test to say `How good are we?' ''
</P>
<P>
   __ Rough record: USC is only 2-3 at the Coliseum against Arizona
State, with the victories occurring in 1980 and 1995. Overall, the
Sun Devils lead the series 8-6, the only Pacific-10 Conference team
to have a winning record against USC.
</P>
<P>
   __ Cal game set: The starting time for USC's game with
California on Oct. 10 will be 3:30 p.m. at the Coliseum. The game
will be telecast on Fox Sports West 2.
</P>
<P>
   __ Check exchange: USC was paid $250,000 by Florida State for
its trip to Tallahassee. That help makes up for the $150,000
settlement USC paid Florida State last year when women's basketball
coach Chris Gobrecht left the Seminoles to come to USC.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
