A9786 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GLENN-HOTWHEEL30-COX     09-29 0303
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GLENN-HOTWHEEL30-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   By Jim Bohman DAYTON DAILY NEWS
</P>
<P>
   If John Glenn's Space Shuttle ride into orbit next month fails
to enhance his image as a space hero, a new Hot Wheels toy from
Mattel might make Ohio's senior senator a collectible.
</P>
<P>
   Mattel will introduce the ``Action Pack John Glenn, Great
American Hero'' miniature toy collection next month in conjunction
with the Oct. 29 launch of the Space Shuttle Discovery for Mission
STS-95.
</P>
<P>
   Glenn, 77, will be part of a seven-member crew that will study
the effects of space flight on aging. He will be the oldest human
to venture into the cosmos and also will serve as official
photographer.
</P>
<P>
   The Hot Wheels package includes a 3-inch miniature of the Space
Shuttle, a 2-inch model of Glenn's 1962 Friendship 7 space capsule
_ complete with window _ in which he was the first American to
orbit the Earth, and smaller miniatures of Glenn as a Mercury
astronaut, U.S. senator and 1998 Space Shuttle crew member.
Suggested retail price for the packaged set, which was made in
China, is $4.95.
</P>
<P>
   An aide said the senator will receive no compensation for the
use of his image.
</P>
<P>
   ``We hope this will benefit the space program by getting kids
excited about it,'' said spokesman Jack Sparks in Washington.
``It's designed for ages 6 to 10.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Senator Glenn said he would approve of it so long as NASA
approved and there was an educational component,'' Sparks said. The
package describes Glenn's career as an astronaut and U.S. senator.
The first Ohioan to win four consecutive terms in the U.S. Senate,
Glenn leaves office this year.
</P>
<P>
   The toy has one minor flaw. The voyage is scheduled to last only
nine days, not 10, as stated on the package.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
