<P>
   KOSOVO-MASSACRE (Gornji Obrinje, Serbia) _ The bodies of 15
women, children and old people of the Deliaj clan lay slumped among
the rocks and streams of the gorge below their village in Kosovo on
Tuesday, their heads shot at close range and in some cases their
bodies mutilated as they tried to escape advancing Serb forces. By
Jane Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   With photo and locator map.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-DISSENT (Beijing) _ A small group of dissident
intellectuals here has issued a sharp challenge to the government,
circulating manifestos on freedom and social justice that reject in
scathing terms many hallowed tenets of the Communist Party. By Erik
Eckholm.
</P>
