three games, but will face its biggest test of the season Saturday
at LSU. Led by All-American running back Kevin Faulk, LSU has one
of the highest strong offenses in the nation. Despite Faulk's
efforts, the key for Georgia could be containing LSU quarterback
Herb Tyler, who has had strong performances in big games in the
past. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   300-YARD-GAME30 _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Ricky Williams claims he could
have carried another 15 times Saturday night against the Rice Owls,
but a deal is a deal. Texas Coach Mack Brown, told late in the game
that his senior halfback was within striking distance of his first
300-yard game, approached Williams with the offer of one more
series. ``He winked at me and smiled,'' Brown said.
</P>
<P>
   (Wangrin, Austin American-Statesman.) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
