<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Hughleys,' `Jesse' get a big hello
 &HT;    By Bob Longino, Phil Kloer, Lyle V. Harris, and Drew Jubera
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   New shows scoring big in the season's first Nielsen ratings
include NBC's ``Jesse'' with Christina Applegate and ABC's ``The
Hughleys'' with D.L. Hughley.
</P>
<P>
   More ratings winners: ``Friends,'' ``The King of Queens'' and
``Everybody Loves Raymond.''
</P>
<P>
   Among the losers: Fox's ``Living in Captivity'' and
``Costello.''
</P>
<P>
   NEW TONIGHT
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Maggie Winters'' 8:30 p.m. EDT CBS _ Faith Ford valiantly
portrays a woman returning to her hometown and finding her old pals
reliving the high school years. Grade: D-
</P>
<P>
   -- ``To Have &AMP; To Hold'' 9 p.m. EDT CBS _ She's a lawyer, he's a
cop. Maybe their love will last, but their show sure won't. Grade:
D+
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Secret Lives of Men'' 9:30 p.m. EDT ABC _ Divorce in
all its unending hilarity. Grade: C
</P>
<P>
   PULL THE PLUG ALREADY
</P>
<P>
   Some old shows deserve to die:
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Nanny'' 8 p.m. EDT CBS _ Somebody ... please ... shut
... her ... up.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Chicago Hope'' 10 p.m. EDT CBS _ With ``Seinfeld'' reruns,
who needs it?
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
