<P>
   EARNINGS-CRUNCH (Boston) -- America's leading corporations face
the worst quarter of earnings in years. The world economic crisis
is eroding the profits of the big multinationals, including
Gillette, Coca-Cola, Procter &AMP; Gamble and others. By Chris Reidy.
1000 words.
</P>
