   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-INDIANS (Cleveland) _ Capitalizing on the batting of
Mo Vaughn and Nomar Garciaparra, the Red Sox end a 13-game
postseason jinx by defeating the Indians 11-3. By Gordon Edes.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   BBA-SHAUGHNESSY-COLUMN (Cleveland) _ The best season in baseball
history won't be complete until we have Fenway and Wrigley playing
host to the duelling jinxes of the Red Sox and Cubs. By Dan
Shaughnessy.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   BBA-RYAN-COLUMN (Cleveland) _ Mo Vaughan's day in Cleveland was
made in free-agency heaven. By Bob Ryan.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-RANGERS-YANKS (New York) -- By Peter May
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   BBA-COMMENT (New York) -- By Larry Whiteside.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
