u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI &LR;      09-29 0497
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Wednesday, Sept. 30, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   LIFE-PLANETS (Seattle) The University of Washington is about to
launch a new Ph.D. program for students who want to hunt for life
on other planets. The new program, the first of its kind in the
nation, is being funded with a 5-year, $2 million grant from the
National Science Foundation and a $500,000 grant from the
University. It will draw together 11 different disciplines ranging
from Astronomy to Microbiology.
</P>
<P>
   By Carol Smith. (story will move in the ``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-WOODARD (Seattle) Ron Woodard, forced out earlier this
month as president of Boeing Commercial Airplane Group, has decided
to retire effective Nov. 1, the company announced Tuesday. Woodard
has not announced what he plans to do next, and was not available
for comment Tuesday, Boeing spokeswoman Sherry Nebel said. However,
industry analysts say his long experience in the aerospace industry
should guarantee him another high-profile job.
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (story will move in the ``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-COLUMN-VECSEY (Seattle) The Mariners are out of the
playoffs, collectively anyway. But Seattle fans can turn on any
playoff game and see some of their former heroes wearing other
uniforms. Bar-hopping with M's fans to get a feel for how they're
taking to vicarious playoff-watching.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS-MARTINEZ (Seattle) Mariners announce they will pick
up their option on Edgar Martinez, meaning that the designated
hitter will play the 1999 season in Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   By Dan Raley. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKW-REIGN-STARBIRD (Seattle) Seattle Reign has first practice
open to the media. Kate Starbird, the rail-thin homegrown star who
was college basketball's player of the year, supposedly is bigger
and stronger after being pushed around her rookie pro season.
</P>
<P>
   By Tyler Kepner. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SEAHAKWS-SIMMONS (Seattle) Anthony Simmons, the Seahawks'
No. 1 draft choice, has been held back by injuries and
circumstances. Instead of challenging for the starting role at
inside linebacker, he's been injured, then moved outside and
relegated to special teams. It's a tough adjustment for a college
star.
</P>
<P>
   By Dan Raley. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-COUGARS (Undated) WSU coach Mike Price announces that Steve
Birnbaum, despite his shaky performance at Cal, will be the team's
starting quarterback Saturday at UCLA. WSU notebook.
</P>
<P>
   By Angelo Bruscas. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS-MCMILLAN (Seattle) The Sonics have named Nate
McMillan an assistant coach.
</P>
<P>
   By Ronald Tillery. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
