   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   SCI-STARBURST-EARTH (Undated) _ NASA announces that a giant
burst of gamma and X-ray radiation hit Earth's ionosphere on Aug.
27. It caused no health problems, but it was the first time a
significant change in Earth's atmosphere has been traced to a
distant star. By John Noble Wiflord. (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m.
ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-BRADLEY (Los Angeles) _ Tom Bradley, the sharecropper's son
who became mayor of Los Angeles and presided over the city for two
decades of explosive growth and change, died Tuesday in Los Angeles
at 80. By Jane Fritsch. (The obit has moved in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
