</P>
<P>
   1998 19-9 4.85 219.0 62 136
</P>
<P>
   NO. 3 STARTER: Kerry Wood
</P>
<P>
   Wood was Chicago's most productive pitcher, with 233 strikeouts
in just 26 starts, but he hasn't pitched since Aug. 31 and is
questionable for this series with a sore elbow. If Wood can't go,
the Cubs will use Steve Traschel, Monday's winner, for Game 3, with
Terry Mulholland, who saved Chicago down the stretch, available as
a spot starter.
</P>
<P>
   Wood W-L ERA IP BB SO
</P>
<P>
   Vs. Braves 1-0 2.18 20.2 16 30
</P>
<P>
   1998 13-6 3.40 166.2 85 233
</P>
<P>
   BULLPEN: Rod Beck
</P>
<P>
   Closer Rod Beck appeared to tire at times during the season, but
he still finished with 51 saves, only the fifth player in
major-league history to reach that number. He can be awfully tough
against the Braves: Andres Galarraga has just three hits against
him in 15 at-bats, while Ryan Klesko is 0-for-6 and Keith Lockhart
is 0-for-4. On the other hand, Chipper Jones is 4-for-7 against
Beck, and Javier Lopez is 4-for-6. For his career, Beck has 16
saves in 20 opportunities against Atlanta. Cubs setup men Terry
Adams and Felix Heredia have struggled lately, particularly Adams.
</P>
