<SLUG> BC-HKN-STARS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STARS REVISIT MEMORY LANE IN EXHIBITION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
By MIKE HEIKA 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Stars coach Ken Hitchcock was a little leery when the topic came
up concerning crowd reaction during tonight's trip to Minneapolis
for a neutral-site clash with the Phoenix Coyotes.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if we're going to be cheered or booed,''
Hitchcock said of the Stars' 7 p.m. preseason game at the Target
Center.
</P>
<P>
   The Stars are returning to their roots, traveling back to the
place where they started as the Minnesota North Stars in 1968.
However, the once-beloved team in hockey-mad Minnesota became
somewhat hated when the organization moved to Texas in 1993, with
owner Norman Green citing a failure to make a profit in the Land of
10,000 Lakes.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think they'll boo me, I hope not,'' said center Mike
Modano, one of few Stars players who remain from the North Stars'
roster. ``They'd boo Norm Green, but I don't think they'd boo the
players. They know it wasn't our fault the team moved.''
</P>
<P>
   Modano and Craig Ludwig are the only former North Stars
scheduled to make the trip. Derian Hatcher is serving out the third
game of a four-game suspension, while Richard Matvichuk is nursing
a knee injury.
</P>
<P>
   Winger Brett Hull makes his summer home in Duluth, Minn., and
said he will have friends and family in attendance.
</P>
<P>
   The only other Stars player with Minnesota ties _ restricted
free-agent winger Jamie Langenbrunner _ is at home in Duluth and
has not yet signed a contract with the Stars. As of yesterday,
Stars general manager Bob Gainey said he did not have plans to meet
with Langenbrunner while in Minnesota. &QL; 
SPEEDY RECOVERY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Defenseman Matvichuk could return to play as soon as
mid-October, Hitchcock said yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   ``Matvichuk is way, way ahead of schedule,'' Hitchcock said.
``We'll see where he is on the weekend, but I look for him to be
available by the middle of October.''
</P>
<P>
   Matvichuk's recovery is amazing considering he had the anterior
cruciate ligament in his left knee replaced June 23 and orginally
was given a recovery period of six months. &QL; 
SYDOR PRACTICES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Defenseman Darryl Sydor returned to practice yesterday after
missing the first two weeks of the preseason because of a contract
squabble.
</P>
<P>
   As for any battle with rookie Sergey Gusev for a place in the
lineup, he said: ``I can't just think there's a place waiting for
me. I have to work and I have to earn it. Whoever is playing well
is going to play, and that's the way it should be.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-29-98 2157EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
