<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-BRITAIN-LABOR-NYT, which moved
in ``i'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``We would rather be popular than unpopular, but it is better to
be unpopular than wrong.''
</P>
<P>
   _PRIME MINISTER TONY BLAIR of Britain, at his Labor Party's
conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
