<SLUG> BC-MERRILL-LAYOFFS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MERRILL SAID TO CONSIDER BOND-UNIT LAYOFFS 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co., which is considering layoffs
because of the recent turbulence in financial markets, may cut as
many as 15 percent, or about 350, of the more than 2,500 people it
employs in its bond businesses, officials at the firm who declined
to be identified said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Merrill, like other big Wall Street firms, is reviewing its
costs because of the downturn in many financial businesses in the
last two months _ including the sales, trading and marketing of
bonds and of most emerging-markets securities.
</P>
<P>
   It is expected that any cuts would fall more on these areas
because they have seen such a drastic decline in business volume,
people at Merrill and other Wall Street firms said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``No final decisions have been made,'' Bill Halldin, a spokesman
for Merrill Lynch, said in reply to questions about layoffs at the
firm and in specific businesses within it.
</P>
<P>
   Merrill, one of the biggest brokerage houses, employs about
60,000 people worldwide.
</P>
<P>
   Merrill is expected to announce its results for the three months
ended Sept. 30 on Oct. 13. Wall Street analysts expect that it
might announce job cuts at that time.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
